9%8E%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n7969","headword_ar":"تحسّر","root":"Hsr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the plumage of a bird, A, and the fur, or soft hair, of a camel, S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell off;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K;) when relating to the fur, or soft hair, of a camel, [said to be]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by reason of fatigue;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) but this restriction is not necessary; for its falling off is sometimes occasioned by diseases; though it may be said that the former cause is the more common. (TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~r Alwabaru Eani","text_ar":"تحسّر الوَبَرُ عَنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbaEiyri","text_ar":"البَعِيرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soft hair, fell off from the camel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner one says of the plumage from the birds: (A:) and of the hair from the ass. (TA.) See also 2. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tHs~rt bayona yadayohi","text_ar":"تحسّرت بَيْنَ يَدَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She uncovered herself,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her head and forehead,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"her face, before him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAsirN","text_ar":"حَاسِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she sat before him with her face uncovered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad.)       -A2-  See also 1, in two places."}],"source_refs":["A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}